InputData.html: Some Swarming Automation Inspiration
DMS Overview

1. Cluster Load Balancing Automation

Swarm around elements in the DMS to balance the number of elements per agent. Non-Swarmable elements are left on their agent but are considered in the count. If there are ties, the element is prefered to stay on the host it's already on to minimize the number of Swarms.

2. Agent Maintenance Automation

Swarm away all elements from the selected agents in the grid below. They will be load balanced by element count between the non-selected agents.

InputData.html:
3. Snapshot Automation

Save a snapshot of the current hosting agent per element. This is done by setting the 'Cluster Maintenace Home DataMiner ID' property on the element with the DataMiner ID of the agent its currently hosted on.
Restore the selected agents to the latest snapshot. This will swarm elements from cluster who were on the selected agents during the last snapshot.
